Package edu.cuny.util

General utility classes.

See:
          Description

Interface Summary
Distribution Defines the operations on the distribution of samples of some random variable.
NumberComparator An interface defining different ways to compare numbers.
ObjectRegistry An interface for object registry, where the references are stored to all sorts of objects so as to avoid direct references between objects.
ParameterDatabaseListener This is a modified version of the class from the original ECJ package by Sean Luke, et al..
Parameterizable Classes implementing this interface indicate that they can be initialized from a parameter database using the "Clique" pattern of ECJ.
Prototypeable This defines an interface for deep cloning.
Resetable Classes implementing this interface indicate that their status is resetable.
ResourceFactory<R> An interface for creating all kinds of resources.
 

Class Summary
ApproxNumberComparator A comparator for double values allowing rounding error to a certain degree.
BaseNIterator An iterator that enumerates the base N representation of every non-negative integer that can be represented within the specified number of digits.
BrowserLauncher provides utitlies to launch a web browser from a Java application on various platforms, Windows, Mac, or Linux.
ColorNameTable defines a table mapping readable names to Colors.
CumulativeDistribution A utility class for cumulative tracking of stats for a series of doubles.
DistributionFactory This defines a factory class that creates AbstractDistributions.
DistributionFactory.Cumulative This defines a factory class that creates CumulativeDistributions.
DistributionFactory.Heavyweight This defines a factory class that creates HeavyweightDistributions.
ExactNumberComparator A comparator for double values allowing no rounding errors.
FixedLengthQueue A queue with fixed length, which can be useful when tracking a sliding window on a data series
Galaxy An implementation of ObjectRegistry that uses Map.
GenericReflection Utility class for handling reflection.
HeavyweightDistribution An distribution which keeps actual cases in memory as well as updating moments dynamically.
IdAllocator Utility class for handing out unique ids.
MathUtil Miscalleneous mathematical functions.
Parameter A Parameter is an object which the ParameterDatabase class uses as a key to associate with strings, forming a key-value pair.
ParameterDatabase This extension of the Properties class allows you to set, get, and delete Parameters in a hierarchical tree-like database.
ParameterDatabaseAdapter This is a modified version of the class from the original ECJ package by Sean Luke, et al..
ParameterDatabaseEvent This is a modified version of the class from the original ECJ package by Sean Luke, et al..
ParameterDatabaseTreeModel This is a modified version of the class from the original ECJ package by Sean Luke, et al..
Partitioner A class that iterates over all numerical partitions of n into k distinct parts including commutative duplications and parts containing zero.
ResourcePool<R> A class for maintaining resources in a pool.
SortedTreeList<E extends Comparable<E>> A tree-based sorted list.
SyncTask A class enabling one task to wait until a certain number of events of specified type occur.
Utils A collection of utility functions.
 

Exception Summary
BadParameterException Thrown when you attempt to create a Parameter from bad path items.
ParamClassLoadException This exception is thrown by the Parameter Database when it fails to locate and load a class specified by a given parameter as requested.
